libbc-concurrency (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add libFuzzer harness infrastructure under fuzzing/ with a new
    harness for the MPMC queue (push/pop/close/is_closed/capacity
    against fuzzer-driven op sequences). Existing dispatch harness
    kept. Single-threaded under asan+ubsan; a dedicated TSAN race
    harness is a follow-up.
  * Gated by -Dfuzzing=true and -fsanitize=fuzzer when CC=clang.
    No public API change.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Wed, 22 Apr 2026 08:00:00 +0000

libbc-concurrency (1.0.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Replace work_ready/work_done atomic+futex signaling with
    pthread_mutex + two condition variables (ready_cond, done_cond)
    sharing a single state_mutex. ThreadSanitizer on gcc 13
    ubuntu-24.04 cannot track happens-before through raw futex
    syscalls; pthread primitives are tsan-native. Closes the
    remaining tsan data races in downstream consumers (bc-hash
    walk_parallel foreach_slot reads, dispatch_batch_iteration,
    error_collector flush).
  * foreach_slot locks/unlocks each worker's state_mutex before
    iterating to re-establish an acquire fence at the slot read
    site.
  * No measurable performance impact on bc-hash bench (13G / 724k
    files corpus): sha256 1.85s (2.35x vs sha256sum -P16), crc32c
    1.02s (3.98x vs cksum -P16), xxh3 1.01s (3.79x vs xxhsum -P16).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 15:00:00 +0000

libbc-concurrency (1.0.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix data race (tsan) on worker slot reads via foreach_slot.
    After dispatch_and_wait, foreach_slot now re-acquires work_done
    on each worker before reading its slot, ensuring tsan-visible
    happens-before for callers that read worker-produced pointers
    or buffers (e.g. bc-hash error_collector flush).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000

libbc-concurrency (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Worker pool: MPMC queue-backed, configurable worker count,
    per-slot lifetime callbacks.
  * Typed dispatch and shared cross-worker context.
  * Signal-safe shutdown coordination.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
